<recipe>
<title>
Caprese Chicken Recipe
</title>
<details>
AUTHOR: i heart eating
PREP TIME: 8 minutes
COOK TIME: 22 minutes
TOTAL TIME: 30 minutes
COURSE: Main Course
CUISINE: Italian
SERVINGS: 4 servings
</details>
<ingredients><ingredient amount="1.0 Tablespoon">Olive Oil</ingredient><ingredient amount="4.0 Pound">Chicken</ingredient><ingredient amount="1.0 Teaspoon">Ital</ingredient><ingredient amount="">Pepper</ingredient><ingredient amount="1.0 Tablespoon">Sugar</ingredient><ingredient amount="4.0">Garlic</ingredient><ingredient amount="1.0 Cup">Grape Tomato</ingredient></ingredients>
<instructions>
Heat a large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add olive oil.
Season chicken with Italian seasoning, salt, and pepper.
Add chicken to pan, and cook until golden and cooked through, about 6-8 minutes per side.
Transfer cooked chicken to a plate.
Reduce heat to medium-low.
Add balsamic vinegar and brown sugar to skillet, and stir to combine.
Stir in garlic, and cook for 1 minute.
Add tomatoes. and season with salt.
Let tomatoes simmer until soft, 6-7 minutes.
Stir in half basil.
Return chicken to skillet.
Top with mozzarella, and cover to melt cheese.
Spoon tomatoes over chicken and sprinkle with remaining basil before serving.
</instructions>
<cuisine>Italian</cuisine></recipe>